<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{2}{y}={47}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{7}{y}=-{72}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{7}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left(-{7}{x}+{2}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left({47}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({6}\right)}{x}+{1.7142857142857}{y}={40.285714285714}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{7}{y}=-{72}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5.2857142857143}{y}=-{31.714285714286}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{31.714285714286}}{{-{{5.2857142857143}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{2}{\left({6}\right)}={47}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{\left({12}\right)}={47}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={47}-{\left({12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{35}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

